726811f-a.title: Queens: Grand Central Parkwa - 69th Road
726811f-a.text:
Grand Central Parkway, north from about 69th Road, showing
the route where the highway was later constructed. View 2 shows
the course of the Parkway, seen in a different direction.
October 1, 1935
Views 1,2

726614f-b.title: Queens: 69th Road - Grand Central Parkway
726614f-b.text:
Flushing Meadow Park (Queens): Viewing southeastward across
the marshes of the lower end of the park, from about 69th Road
and Grand Central Parkway. In the background are the car yards
and repair shops of the Independent System Subway. When this
area later became part of the grounds of the New York Worldts
Fair of 1939-40 an artificial lake--Willow Lake--was crested
here.
View 3 shows construction operations.
Views 1-2: October 1,1935
View 3: February 10,1937
P. L. Sperr
